values:
Shaun and I have been doing so much better since we talked about everything and got it all out. I've felt closer to him and lighter and I feel like I can ask him anything or talk to him about whatever is on my mind. THis is how it should have been, but wasn't. I'm glad that we are doing well.
in other news. I leave for europe in 19 days. I'm so freaking nervous. Oh my god, I'm freaking out. I just know that something is going to go wrong or we're going to miss a flight or something crazy. I guess I freak out every single time but still, this is the first non academic outside of the country trip I've been on, and me and my friends have planned it all, so if it goes wrong there is nobody to blame but myself.

RELATIONSHIP DRAMA

So Shaun and I broke up for a day and then got back together. This all started over a phone bill. Our bill was forty dollars more than it is every other month so I looked at my portion to see who I was calling and texting so much. Wasn't my problem. 120 ish pages of our 167 page phone bill were all text messages on his part. They were all to the same two numbers.. all day everyday he was texting these two numbers. I found out that one was his friend ashley from work and the other was some girl mai he knows that lives in cleveland. I am not a jealous or insecure girlfriend, I do not mind that he has friends that are girls because I have friends that are boys. A healthy relationship does not soley consist of eachother.. it involves friends of both sexes. And I know and accept that. But he was calling these numbers at like 4 in the morning while he was at work and talking for like 30 minutes. and then calling them again when I thought he was sleeping, or after he left my house.  At one point he talked to his friend in cleveland for 70 minutes. I never thought he was cheating on me and he wasn't because he is a good person. It just shined a light on the fact that he was talking to them more than he was talking to me. It really hurt my feelings and offended me, it also opened up a can of worms. We got into all the things that were bothering us and we never told eachother, which is not a good part of a relationship. So we talked everything out and I said that while we were working on our problems it would really make me feel a lot better if he wouldn't talk to the girl in cleveland. (eventhough i know they are just friends)I asked him to cut back on texting because that's what he went over on and why our phone bill was so expensive. I can't ask him to stop talking to his friend ashley from work because they work together it's not like I can say just don't look at any other girl, that would be crazy.
It still hurt my feelings. He felt like he couldn't talk about things with me because he though that I wouldn't care. Which is something I need to work on. But I think it was inappropriate for him to be talking to these girls at the hours that he was talking to them, eventhough he works third shift and they may be awake at the times when he would be awake, and I may not. It felt weird to me, although he saw it differently. He didn't think there was anything wrong with it because he wasn't looking to cheat on me with any of them, it still made me really sad.
It also bothered me that one of the girls calls him every now and again when she gets drunk. I really don't think that's appropriate. I cannot deny that I have drunk dialed my friends, but they are usually of the same sex and the ones that weren't, were calls that I shouldn't have made because when you're not in your sound mind you really shouldn't be calling other people's boyfriends. I know that's probably not why she called but it just bothers me a little. anyways, we worked out things and I know it's not perfect but it's a start.
Plus we leave for europe soon and it's been tough on both of us trying to save up money and get everything ready.

THIS WEEKEND

one of the main things I asked Shaun to do was to give me more gestures. We don't have to buy eachother exepnsive things every day or anything like that just let eachother know that we're thinking about the other one or just do awesome and nice things for eachother. 
so this weekend on Friday after I worked a double Shaun and I went to a bar with Jeremy and Liz and had a good time listening to the band anddrinking and people watching, which was fun because it's something we don't often do. 
Last night after I worked a double again he came over and gave me some lillies (one of my favorite flowers) and took me downtown. We had coffee at Kaldi's then walked down the street to Vynl, a diner (a very nice... semi pretentious diner) and had some food. It had a really awesome atmosphere, so I would go back, but I would probably go back to have cocktails or something. Then we went to his apartment and made some more food (because the food at vynl, although good wasn't filling)
Then today Tina, Shaun and I went to the museum to see the Pirate exhibit. So this weekend was really cool.

"I lace my Chucks, I walk the aisle
I take my pills, the babies cry
All I hear is what's playing through
The in-flight radio
Now every word of every song
I ever heard that made me wanna stay
Is what's playing through
The in-flight radio, and I
And I am, finally waking up"
-Jack's Mannequin

i totalled my car. what a mess... i f'ing hate this shit. if it's not one thing it's another.
i'm leaving in less than five weeks and i still don't have all of the money i need... and i still haven't practice packed as many times as i should have. 
lacey and i are planning to move out in february.. we would be taking over her sisters lease in an apartment in newport (historic sector) if all goes well... it's really unique and cute. 


if anyone knows of anyone who is hiring for a day shift job for the summer in the cincinnati area let me know!

How well do you know your next-door neighbors?

i can usually recall their firstnames. their last name is totally lost to me.

it's been fricking forever since i have used livejournal. i really don't know why i haven't written in here i always have these great thoughts i need to get out and never do it...that was slightly sarcastic. but anyways a  quick update on me. I will be graduating in a little over a year in German Studies and Spanish with a Certificate in Business Spanish. taht will be exciting when i can't find a job. 
I will be traveling this summer to London, Berlin and Barcelona. WHich i am really excited about. It should be a flipping blast, with Shaun, Lacey and Clark.
Motion City Soundtrack really has it correct with their song "the future freaks me out" because seriuosly I'm a little panic-attacky lately with all the stuff that's been changin in my own life, my friends lives, the world etc. 
I found out another person from oak hills died. I hope his family is able to heal from such a tragic event. 


I seated ugliness on my knee, and almost immediately grew tired of it. 
Salvador Dali

RULES: Each player of this game starts off with 10 weird things/habits/little known facts about yourself. People who get tagged need to write a blog of their own 10 weird habits/things/little known facts as well as state this rule clearly. At the end you need to choose 10 people to be tagged and list their names. No tag backs.. (If you've already been tagged, you're off the hook.)


1. My boyfriend calls me Monk. (from the TV show.) because I have what I call lazy OCD, it's not bad enough to make me rock back in forth in the corner. Things make me awkwardly uncomfortable like when things aren't in a straight line, or when people try on my shoes and then don't put them back in the right position, oh oh or when one pullstring on a sweatshirt/shoestring isn't at the exact level as the other. And I always ALWAYS have to eat everything in a specific order, counting how many bites of each thing I've had and how many swallows of drink I can have.  

2. When I'm tired i speak a combination of German/Spanish/American/Jamie that isn't highly understood unless one knows all four languages. 

3. I chose my ringtone because it sounds like a rave. When it starts ringing there is a part where it's just an escalating noise and during that noise i say "AAAAAAAANNNDDDD.... RAVE!" and once the music hits my boyfriend and i dance around rave/glowstick style while saying "UNS UNS UNS".. you know, the rave sound.

4. I was handed a card by a drunk german in Munich that said  (and i'm translating here) "i am looking for an American woman to dominate me. if you know anyone who wants to be worshipped please let me know so that i may marry her. I kiss feet" Fortunately for everyone involved we all had boyfriends so we just laughed the card away and tried to shake drunky mcgermanson off.

5. I used to play in oil pits with my friends tina mandy and carly. i also used to throw mud at our apartment buildings. 


6. One time at UC my friend Michael made me laugh so hard I peed myself a little. But i never told him because that's embarassing. so instead i posted it on here so that everyone could know.

7. Everytime I try to skip class I wind up walking straight into my teacher. Literally. Every time.

8. People think I look like Molly Shannon. One time a guy came up to me and said "could you just do me one favor." I almost whipped out my Matrix-ocity on him but then he said "could you put your hands in your armpits and then sniff them loudly" so i did. and everyone laughed. I should join the circus.

9. I don't believe in soulmates. 

10. I love watching foreign movies. 

and this is supposedly the part where i tag people.
i don't know how to do that so i'll say their names
tina funk
joie bucalo
laura bingle
christina dole
mandy funk

i honestly think those are the only friends i have on here that haven't done this already

it really irks my tater when 
a) someone sneezes and I  bless them and then they don't say thank you
b) i sneeze and no one says bless you

what the heck happened to traditional manners. is it so much to ask? If we were native americans, me saying bless you is saving your soul from escaping from your body.
Thats a big frickin deal.

wow it's been awhile. so far all i've done is start school and keep working a the big Rosa's. 
my boyfriend had a fight the other day. and then we stopped fighting and decided to do something about it. i'm pretty sure it stems from neither of us having any money to do anything nice for the other. but that's ok. i know we'll get out of the rut. in december it will be 2 and a half years. damn that's a long time. i wonder what we'll do for our three year anniversary. i kinda felt bad this year because i was leaving for germany and we didn't get to spend much time with eachother on our anniversary. but this year hopefully will be different. hopefully i am not out of the country on that day. here are my options for this summer
scotland with lacey, shaun and clark for the harry potter premier + mexico with church
or
queretaro, mexico for six weeks taking a class
or
salamanca, spain for 5 weeks taking a class

i miss germany

why do we celebrate columbus day? 

the other day mandy brought leigha to school and i hung out with them for a spell. it was great. leigha grows up more everytime isee her. she's beautiful. if i knew how to post a picture i would. i think she finally recognizes me because she doesn't see me everyday but this time i saw her and she started laughing. it made me feel really good. i want a kid.

i met this girl in my spanish class who is from the ukraine originally and it was really cool. I feel bad for people who meet me sometimes when they are from other countries because i like to pump them with questions. I love meeting people from other countries and other cultures. I went to "white suburbia school" for high school where there wasn't a whole lot of diversity. a million kids but nto a lot of diversity, so now at college i have a milllion questions when i meet new people. luckily she wasn't offended or anything. This girl i work with at larosa's, her family is actually from Gana and i asked her a million questions too, haha she said that if an american were to go to gana the people there would be doing exactly what i was doing to her and asking her all kinds of stuff and she said they would be like "wooooaaah your from america? really?!"

i wish i could get my parents to plan a trip across the seas.

jamie
"Just ask your mama, she knows"

Yesterday I went to the Gap Outlet in Hebron, KY. i was taking Shaun there for his first outlet experience. I found some cute stuff to try on. little did i know i was about to be ROBBED BLIND!
I went into the dressing room and tried on my garments. I gave the lady my garments that i did not want and walked out of the dressing room. about 10 seconds later I realized that I had forgotten my purse in the dressing room. So i turned immediately around. I said, I left my purse in the room and the woman who helped me was walking out of the storage room with it in her hand. I guess she heard me say that i had left it. She handed it to me. It was open. and so was my change purse. my 80 dollars was missing. I flipped out. The dressing room attendant who gave me my purse said that a woman with blonde hair found the purse and that i should look for her. We frantically look around the store., and get a manager involved. well then this tall blonde had sandy brown hair and had a bunch of kids with her. then she changed into a sandy brown haired woman with two kids who was only a little taller than me. I'm not tall.
i didn't catch on that anything was amiss in her story until later reflection. 
as we are searching i realize that my boyfriend had abandoned me and was talking to the manager and the other dressing room attendent far away. so i left and the other girl went back to her job in the fitting room.
i join their conversation and realize that the dressing room attendent who made up this huge long story about some woman who stole my money (and also told me how low it was for someone to steal money out of someone else's purse) was actually carrying a fat wad of something in her back pocket. the other fitting room attendent said she saw no such woman and the manager checked the storage cameras to see if they could see anything.
we waited while she was checking. she came back and said that she sees her go back with my purse into the storage room and bend down with it.. looking all suspicious-like. but since she didn't see her actually take the money out of my purse that they can't do anything. she said i am welcome to call the police and they can actually do something. I decided i might as well try. i called some cop and he came over and i told him exactly how many 20's and 10's i had and he disappeared to the back of the store in the fitting room for about 20 minutes. he came back and said "follow me ma'am" we went outside and he handed me my 80 dollars! 
he said that the manager was in the back firing the girl who stole the money from my purse and apparently they didn't do a very thorough background check because she had done some serious time in a woman's institution and was wanted for escaping. when we left the cop was trying to get a warrant for her arrest. 
wow.
that was a crazy day.
so by all means watch your shit.

another member of the 2003 Oak Hills graduating class died. Tim Roos was killed in Iraq. I feel so terrible for his family, wife and two week old daughter. Tim Roos was friends with Zach Moody, who I was friends with, and all of us hung out a couple of times.. this was like years ago. It surprised me when I heard he became a marine but then again i didnt know him that well.
i hate that as we get older things like this happen more frequently. 
This war needs to end so that people like Tim Roos can return home to their families.

I leave for Germany on Friday so I won't be able to update for a montyh. not that that has never happened before. but I will be in Munich until july 7. in dublin until july 12 and in london until july 15. then i come home
today is shaun and i's two year anniversary. WOW. two years is a long time for me. i'm proud of us! go us!
final notes.
i will miss my friends.
i will miss my boyfriend dearly.
i can't wait to be out of America. 
until i return!

jamie

Is this soley an American problem? Aer people this stupid in Europe? Canada? Mexico? Iceland?
Maybe it's just the fact that i'm stir crazy. maybe it's just Cincinnati but certain Phenomena have been taking place that really make me question what the fuck is going on inside the heads of Americans. 

Today on the way home from school i was slowing to stop at a stop light. Normal. I was probably going about 20mph when this occured:
A teenaged boy (about 17) and two younger girls ( probably about 10) were standing on the side of the rode. Without looking either way the seventeen year old stepped out and would have been hit by my car if he had not come out of whatever GOD FORSAKEN REVERIE that he had placed himself under. He also would have led the unfortunate 10 years to certain injury too. And then (as is the case with most teenagers in America) he glared at me like it was my fault. If i would have ever walked out in front of traffic like that my dad would have yelled at me so fast and so harsh you wouldn't know what hit you. IT was one of the first things i learned as a child. NEVER CROSS THE STREET WITHOUT LOOKING BOTH WAYS. TWICE. and this is saying something because i grew up on a farm in indiana. The closest street was a mile away.

this is just a tiny glimpse into what is going on in the American youth lately. They don't care about anything. They don't care about other people. they don't even care about themselves. We have become too lazy to even get off the damn couch to shut the tv off to notice. WHen i wa sin germany we ran across a self proclaimed anarchist. a bum. unshowevered. with his dog. Yet as we were talking to him we realized he spoke perfect english. and he knew more about the american goverment and it's policies than we did. I was ashamed of myself. HOw could this foreignor know (AND CARE) more about what is going on in my country than me and all of my friends? It's because the goverment has done nothing to stop it. they have encouraged our uninvolvement. They say they want us to vote. they say they want us to know. to understand. But when THEY present US with the candidates for lawmaking they leave us with little choice. they tell us who to vote for. The candidates (in my mind) are rarely ever different. Maybe they mean well. Maybe they even believe what they are saying. But nothing ever gets done. I guess it could be a bias because I am directly speaking of the currenct "american regime". I am sick of the laziness. I am sick of the lack of education. i am sick of the ignorance. I am sick of parents not teaching their children how to properly cross the street. I am sick of seeing 10 year olds dressed as prostitutes. i am then sick of wondering why we have pedophiles when we allow our children to dress like this. (i am also aware that this is not the only reason, i am not that ignorant)
 i am sick of the imigration laws because all of the "illegal" mexicans i know deserve every penny they have worked for and they work 4 times as hard as i ever have en my entire life, and they don't even keep it they give it to their families because that is what is important to them. i am sick of our nation being able to tell someone who they can and cannot marry. I am sick of this country taking away the rights of women. i am sick of the body image in today's media.
 i am sick of president bush and his war. that's right HIS war. i am sick of people killing other people. i am sick of children rotting in jail. i am sick of children's minds rotting in front of the television. i am sick of the bird flu epidemic.
which brings me to

ever notice that every few years we are stricken with some new unstoppable cureless biological phenomenon that we must "prepare ourselves for"? West nile virus. Killer Bees. Avion Flu.  they are all the same. the government needs us to be afraid of these things because we will stand "united" behjnd their sole antidote to whatever horrors are out there. 
i am sick of it. 

dear american government,
I am on to you
Jamie Puckett

fucking global studies grant didn't go through. fuckers. 
but Germany is coming quick.
My 21 birthday is Tuesday. I'm having a party at the HOfbrauhaus. It's going to be jammin'
I've been having some problems with the boyfriend. not really problems but i feel like i've been pushing his buttons every time i get a chance. it's not his fault. I guess on some level i'm just trying to see what he finds ok and what he doesnt. i can't really explain it. like is it ok to talk about this or that etc. Sometimes i don't like the answers. maybe i should just be very honest with him. i think he is afraid of brash honesty because in the past every brash honest thing that was said ended the relationship. (in the case of the ex it would be she HONESTLY liked to lick vagina and didn't so much enjoy the cock) but i don't feel like me saying whatever is on my mind is a bad thing. i have no intention of breaking up with him. it's not so much even a specific thing. i feel like i have to be careful about what i say because it will hurt his feelings. i don't want to hurt his feelings. 
i could be being selfish. i am kinda "in your face" about things and i guess i could be forgetting about his feelings.i should try not to hurt his feelings i guess i can't just be "me me me" with everything i say.  i have found in our relationship that i am prone to forgetting that he is not psychic and dones't know what i'm thinking. poor guy. he's my first serious boyfriend so i have no comparison to say "yeah i don't like when boys do this.. i like when boys do this"
umm... back to germany
I will be stayin in the pension in Munich, the London backpackers hostel in london and Isaacs hostel in Dublin.
So excited it's rediculous.
i've already 'PRACTICE PACKED' like 44444558 times. i love packing. 

today was mother's day. My mommy is great. I feel bad for all those years (aka puberty) when i took her for granted. I really tried to rebel against everything she said. i wasn't a bad kid or anything  but for some reason it was really easy for her to hurt my feelings. she would say "i don't like it when you wear black" so i would wear nothing but because i didn't understand that she wasn't judging  me by what i wore she was worried that i was depressed or something. I remember exasperated conversations when my parents would sit me down and say "we've never had the chance to be a parent to a teenager"
I think i have grown up mentally so much. I now know that my parents aren't exactly as freakish as i thought they were. They are actually occasionally enjoyable to be around, and they are nice enough to let me stay in their house. I am also now thankful for them making me work at an early age. I'm not a spoiled brat. THey don't hand me anything. When i was 14 i had my first job. I made money to buy things. Now i buy my own gas, clothes, food and pay my own bills. i guess what i'm saying is.. maybe it's a good thing they aren't rich. I paid my way when i was 18 to go to germany because they didn't have any money to give me. I'm doing the same thing now except it's a little harder because it's a bigger expense.
what i'm saying is. Thank you mom.
and with this i also have to thank Diane Elkins for being my second mom
jamie

I went to the Hofbrauhaus last night for Miranda's 21st birthday. It was a riot. IT was the best way to end this amazingly stressfull and weird week. Miranda's parents were dancing on the benches at our tables. Me and shaun and Joe were Ho-downing in the aisle ways. WHere else are you ENCOURAGED to stand on the benches, dance like a crazy person, and be loud and obnoxious. It was amazing. I'm pretty sure Miranda's parents drank a keg each. MY voice hurts a little because we kept screaming!

I would suggest everyone have a birthday party their. Or at least go on a Friday night when everyone is loud and riotous. 

Well kids, tomorrow the easter bunny comes. 

Jamie

Kim's funeral was tonight. It felt weird. We pulled into the parking lot and I saw so many familiar faces, some people I didn't know. Some people I knew. I hugged Erin Walsh and some people were telling a couple of Kim stories. I walked in and realized it was the same funeral home that my grandpa's funeral was held at. 
Standing in line, we noticed a board full of pictures of Kim and her friends. I was ok looking at them until I saw one of Me, Kim, Allison, Krystal after an orchestra concert. And then I started to well up because it for some reason hit me that this funeral was for someone that I know. She was a part of my life at one point. We hung out. We talked. We laughed. 
And I was ok until Shana Wahl hugged me. I saw her approaching me and for some reason when she said "you ok?" and hugged me I lost it. I think it was because she was the one who told me about when Kim died.
After I saw her in the casket I was just sitting there thinking about how we REALLY AREN'T GAURENTEED TOMMORROW. I know people say that the deceased don't really look like who they really are. And it's true. That wasn't Kim. Kim was already gone, that was just the vessel Kim used to touch our lives.
I ran into Frau Schott. I ran into Doug Schmaltz. I ran into Jon Meyer. David THielen. Brad Braunstein. Amanda Devoto. Harry Zen. Amber THornes.
These are people that I should see more often. I hate that it was a reunion. I hate that we had to see eachother at a funeral. 
I felt awkward. After getting so upset a bunch of us stood outside and we bullshitted about life and what we were up to and talked and reminisced. It felt so weird to laugh when I had just seen my friend in a casket. But, I don't really think Kim would have liked to see all of her friends puffy eyed and in mourning. At one point A couple of people came out of the funeral home and stood outside sobbing. I felt like such an intruder because we were standing so close. Because, we were still laughing and carrying on I suggested we move away, so that the sobbing people could have space and i didn't want our laughter to mock the hugeness of what was going on.
Jamie
Quote of the day "Little jamie puckett, hoppin' down the bunny trail.." -Kim Freeman

somebody just called me and told me that one of my friends from high school is dead. Kim Freeman. I haven't seen her in so long. I talked to her everyday in classes. We had German exchange students together, and i have a whole page dedicated to her in my senior memory book. She is such a good person, i can't belieive something like this could happen to someone my age. She is one of the most genuine people i have ever met in my life. Was. 
I'll never forget how nice and caring and funny she was. Everyday she made up a new song about me in orchestra and would sing it to me. It always made me laugh.
If this is how bad I feel, I can't imagine what her family and close friends are going through.

On the way home from shaun's apartment while i was driving i was struck by this unsettling thought; people don't change they adapt. People are the same throughout history. One can argue that people are more advanced nowadays, people are smarter, people are less barbaric than the caveman-club-carrying-heman that appears to be where we spawned from. i would say that we haven't really changed one bit since then. And there isn't much difference between a five year old and fifty five year old (besides the noteable appearance and of course the amount of time and experience on this earth. Humans have always had to deal with fear. In the caveman days (forgive my obvious failure to have first hand experience in this matter) i am sure that there was the everyday fear that a wooly mammouth was going to saunter into your cave unnanounced and shank you with it's tusks. Now we live in fear of terrorists sauntering into our country and 'shanking' us with biological weapons. The five year old may be afraid of spiders or the dark but as that five year old goes through the obligatory rites of passages and exchanges childhood for adolescence, and then adolescence for adulthood the fear just molds and conforms itself to that person's lifestyle. Now we are afraid of being alone, we are afraid that our family may be injured on their way to work, some of us are still, myself included, afraid of the dark. 
We, as humans, have also had to learn how to deal with fitting in, or how precisely not to fit in. I'm sure it seems like it must have been easier in the time when our community was made up of the people who we sat by the fire with at night out in a field in front of our cave under the stars. Those people wore the same loinclothes over their genitals that we did, they also had to struggle to survive. The weak were weeded out, it would seem under harsher conditions. now we struggle through our teen years to find out who we are.... we aren't much different than those comparing the size of their clubs by the fire, we just use different things such as cars, houses, and clothes to weed out the "weak." Sometimes early on, we see people with simalar situations and feel comfortable around them. Sometimes much later we fall into our groups of people, some of us may just never find the people with the same second-hand loincloths and battered wooden clubs. but eventually, we usually find where we belong. I, thankfully, have found my people. I am proud to say though that i have many many friends and if lined up side by side not one of them looks the same on the outside. But it's comforting to know that we are all still struggling with the same fears, emotions and limitations that our friends are, and those people who came much much earlier than we did.
